text.tspan: For more on the model selection triple,
Additionally, models are also stored in the
database as pickles, and can be retrieved
and loaded by the web application.
• Routinely (nightly/weekly) join feature tables into an
instance table to create a static snapshot of the data
• Engage the model selection triple to fit one or more models.
• Pickle models and save them back to the database.
Integration happens at the database layer, which we will call a “computational data
store”. The Web app manages transactions on normalized feature tables, which are
joined into an instance table for machine learning.
• Transactional, deal with only a few rows at a time
• Are live, and perform computation on demand
• Must make immediate responses to requests
• Can be interactive and solicit feedback
• Batch analysis: learns by iterating over a single table
• Must be routinely updated to take advantage of feedback
• Once trained, is able to make predictions on new data
